 E  dellingerma vmi edu       El firme amor me diste  Espa a  con tus dones Pablo Neruda   A los sevillanos nos acusan de ombliguismo   pero es que Sevilla tiene un ombligo digno de ver  Antonio Burgos  Que me busquen en Triana si me llegara a perder Sevillanas populares   Mary Ann Dellinger  Professor of Modern Languages and Cultures  joined the VMI faculty in 2001 after completing her Ph D  in Spanish at Arizona State University  A specialist in both Peninsular culture and second language pedagogy  she teaches all levels of Spanish language as well as upper level courses centered on cultural and literary topics with an interdisciplinary focus  Professor Dellinger served as the first Director of the VMI ePortfolio Project  2009 2012  and co founded the  First Year Initiative  pilot program with Dr  Elaine Humphrey  Director of the Miller Academic Center  Dr  Dellinger lived in Spain for eighteen years and returns frequently to the Peninsula  She and her husband live in their Rockbridge County home  Her son  William Antonio  and three grandchildren  Marco  Triana  and Lelia  reside in Phoenix    Dr  Mary Ann Dellinger Home Awards and Honors Courses Publications Conference Papers Professional Citizenship Cadet Development Summer in Spain VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 